SECTION.P:
(B) An intact, native vegetation assemblage that can include, but is not limited to, shadscale saltbush (
Atriplex confertifolia
), black sagebrush (
Artemisia nova
), Nevada mormon tea (
Ephedra nevadensis
), James' galleta (
Hilaria jamesii
 (formerly 
Pleuraphis jamesii
)), and alkali sacaton (
Sporobolus airoides
) to maintain plant-plant interactions and ecosystem resiliency and provide the habitats needed by Tiehm's buckwheat's insect visitors and pollinators.
